# Brand Shop Builder — Skill & Requirements

**When**: Building or modifying Brand Shop pages, modules, or shelf creation flows

**Trigger phrases**: "Brand Shop", "shop builder", "brand page builder", "create a shop", "shelf page"

---

## Overview

The Brand Shop Builder is a 3-panel page builder for creating and editing branded shop experiences. It consists of:

1. **Module List** (left panel) — draggable list of shop modules (hero banner, category hub, skinny banner, item carousel)
2. **Shop Preview** (center panel) — live preview of the assembled brand shop
3. **Module Editor** (right panel) — context-sensitive editor for the selected module's configuration

Additionally, a **Shelf Creation Dialog** allows inline creation of Shelf pages attached to a Brand Shop.

---

## File Structure

All Brand Shop Builder files live under `client/features/brand-shop/`:

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `BrandShopBuilder.tsx` | Main page — shell layout (MastHead + AppSidebar) + 3-panel builder |
| `BrandShopBuilder.module.css` | Page layout styles |
| `ModuleList.tsx` | Left panel — draggable module list with template selector |
| `ModuleList.module.css` | Module list styles |
| `ShopPreview.tsx` | Center panel — live preview rendering of all modules |
| `ShopPreview.module.css` | Preview styles |
| `ModuleEditor.tsx` | Right panel — form editor for hero banner config |
| `ModuleEditor.module.css` | Editor styles |
| `ShelfCreationDialog.tsx` | Modal dialog for creating Shelf pages |
| `ShelfCreationDialog.module.css` | Dialog styles |
| `ShelfStatusTag.tsx` | Status tag component for shelf status display |
| `mockData.ts` | Demo data for the builder |
| `types.ts` | TypeScript interfaces for all data models |

